          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "We were looking for joining my son into school, which teaches concepts in practical way and does not burden kids with education and we came across GEEKZ MICROSCHOOL. It is an awesome school with excellent curriculum. Thanks to Sridhar and Nandini for coming up with such a good curriculum. They emphasize more on English, which is good and they encourage kids to be independent learners.\nThanks to all the educators, they are all friendly and Sujji mam for doing a wonderful job.\nThe village trip organized by the school is really unique and helps kids to know about life in the village and cultivation of crops, games played in the village, bullock cart ride, milking of cow & pottery.\nThe business fair conducted by the school is also very good, where kids learn about doing business in  a fun way.\nThere are much more activities conducted by school filled with learning and fun.\nMy son  Pranav V Chavan enjoys going to school everyday.\nIf you are looking for admissions for your kids then GEEKZ must be your first choice.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
